  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA368-kiḷavi">itu tōḻi talaimakaṟkuc ceṟippaṟivuṟīiyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante informed HIM of confinement.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA368">
<l>            perumpuṉaṅ kavaruñ ciṟukiḷi yōppik</l>
<l>            karuṅkāl vēṅkai yūca ṟūṅkik</l>
<l>            kōṭēn talkuṟ ṟaḻaiyaṇintu nummō</l>
<l>            ṭāṭiṉam varutali ṉiṉiyatu muṇṭō</l>
<l>            neṟipaṭu kūḻaik kārmutir pirunta</l>
<l>            veṟikamaḻ koṇṭa nāṟṟamuñ ciṟiya</l>
<l>            pacalai pāytaru nutalu nōkki</l>
<l>            vaṟituku neñciṉaḷ piṟitoṉṟu cuṭṭi</l>
<l>            veyya vuyirttaṉaḷ yāyē</l>
<l>            yaiya vañciṉa maḷiyam yāmē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>          We played<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">āṭiṉam</term>: here it is even more difficult to understand tradition’s usual <term xml:lang="ta">muṟṟeccam</term>, since in that case in the very least we would expect a second person: <term xml:lang="ta">āṭiṉir</term></note></l>
<l rend="indent3">          with you, adorning [our] hips of eminent curves with foliage,</l>
<l rend="indent3">          hanging in the swing on the black-trunked Vēṅkai tree,</l>
<l rend="indent3">          chasing away the small parrots that seize the big field.</l>
<l rend="indent4">          Is there anything sweeter<note place="foot">Here T.V.G. explains we have to read <term xml:lang="ta">varutaliṉum iṉitu uṇṭō</term> - the word order being changed for metrical reasons. This seems to make sense.</note> than [your] coming?</l>
<l rend="indent3">          Looking at [our] forehead where pallor spreads slightly</l>
<l rend="indent3">          and at the fragrance brought by the fragrant perfume,</l>
<l rend="indent4">          that was, black colour ripening(?), in [our] curly short [hair],</l>
<l rend="indent3">          pointing out something else with a vainly languishing heart</l>
<l>        mother sighed hotly.</l>
<l>        O lord, we have come to fear, pitiable we.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
    </text>
